There are studies that have helped us predict the air quality using neural networks and machine learning. However air quality prediction still has some problems. LSTM-based models by Seng et al. (2021)23 utilized LSTM for spatiotemporal prediction in Beijing but depended on averaged values from stations, thus limiting generalization. Zhang et al. (2021)24 used BiLSTM with EMD to forecast short term \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
